<br>
Alas, you're not asking about high levels!  I know =)  But still as I said earlier at 44 Shock of Steel is your best DD, at 49 you get Lava Bolt (bolt is the key there, hehe) which will be an evoke based 810 damage bolt, not bad just not exactly precise damage.  Between 44 and 57 there are no more conjuration based damage spells, they are all evoke.  Char is a great DD, and I actually use it quite a but - evoke based though.<br>
<br>
Boils down to where you want your savings.  With spec conjure I save on 80% of my spells when spec kicks in (which is quite a bit with Casting Mastery 3).  I can DD, Summon anything in my spellbook, etc for less mana.  Where I hurt is when I want to use a rain spell, but tbh I've never ran outta mana when I've wanted too, and in AE groups I've always had enough mana using Scintillation.<br>
<br>
IMO Spec Conjure is the way to go, but many don't necessarily agree with that =)<br>
